text: Nikolay Timofeyevich Tanayev (; 5 November 1945 â€“ 19 July 2020) was a Kyrgyz politician. He served as the Prime Minister of Kyrgyzstan from 2002 to 2005, under President Askar Akayev. Tanayev was an ethnic Russian. On 19 July 2020, he died in Moscow at the age of 74. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Prime Ministers of Kyrgyzstan
